ridge roof monitors, etc. 

2.14.2 Installation Pathlength. The installation 
flange-to-flange distance. 

2.14.3 Monitoring Pathlength. The effective depth of 
effluent (the distance over which the light beam is actually 
evaluating the stack effluent) measured by the COMS at the 
installation location. Monitoring pathlength is to be used for 
the optical alignment, response, and calibration error tests of 
section 7 and calculation of the pathlength correction factor 
